Title:
Venoma — C++ Cobalt Strike Beacon Dropper with API Hashing and Indirect Syscalls

Type:
GitHub Tool

Short Summary (4–8 sentences max):
- Venoma is a Windows C++ “raw” Cobalt Strike beacon dropper focused on AV/EDR evasion during payload staging and execution.  
- It combines compile-time API hashing and runtime dynamic linking to reduce static indicators (imports/strings) and complicate analysis.  
- The project includes multiple execution and stealth techniques such as PPID spoofing, DLL unhooking (including “Fresh + Perun’s fart”), ETW patching, and indirect syscall execution to bypass user-mode hooks.  
- It supports several payload execution methods (EnumPageFilesW, local/remote APC) and includes self-deletion for post-execution cleanup.  
- It also documents integration with the Cobalt Strike Artifact Kit workflow (renaming to artifact64big.exe and using a custom CNA) to generate stageless Windows payloads.  
- Useful primarily for red teams, pentesters, and malware researchers evaluating defensive coverage and detection gaps around common loader tradecraft.

